OL,3,CVladimir Putin would have ordered
OL,4,CSalisbury Novichok poisoning, inquiry
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMr Allen told an inquiry that the
OL,8,Frisks involved in carrying out such an
OL,9,Foperation on British soil were
OL,10,F"reputationally enormous", and would
OL,11,Fhave required authorisation "at every
OL,12,Flevel".
OL,14,FThe Skripals were poisoned with the
OL,15,Fmilitary grade nerve agent Novichok,
OL,16,Fwhich had been smeared on the front
OL,17,Fdoor handle of their home.
OL,19,FWithin days, the then prime minister
OL,20,FTheresa May had publicly blamed Russia
OL,21,Ffor the attack.
