OL,3,CVladimir Putin would have ordered
OL,4,CSalisbury Novichok poisoning, inquiry
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe inquiry has heard that he may have
OL,8,Ffound it just minutes after it was
OL,9,Fdiscarded by two Russian agents who
OL,10,Fwere trying to assassinate Sergei
OL,11,FSkripal.
OL,13,FMr Allen said that it was unlikely
OL,14,Fthat the Novichok could have been made
OL,15,Fand deployed by "non-state actors",
OL,16,Fbecause the conditions required to
OL,17,Fmake such a "dangerous substance"
OL,18,Findicated that it would need to have
OL,19,Fbeen made in a highly sophisticated
OL,20,Fstate run lab.
