OL,3,CVladimir Putin would have ordered
OL,4,CSalisbury Novichok poisoning, inquiry
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe inquiry heard how Sergei Skripal,
OL,8,Fa former double agent, was "perceived
OL,9,Fto be a traitor" after being tried and
OL,10,Fconvicted of high treason, but may
OL,11,Fhave "believed his (subsequent) pardon
OL,12,Fwould protect him".
OL,14,FHe said he believed that the outcome
OL,15,Fof the operation against Mr Skripal
OL,16,Fwas not intended to remain entirely
OL,17,Fcovert, and that the Russian state
OL,18,Fexpected them to "put two and two
OL,19,Ftogether".
